he outermost feathers. The sexes are alike. Distribution and habitat The slate-throated gnatcatcher is found from central and eastern Panama south through western Colombia into northwestern Ecuador. It inhabits humid primary forest, mature secondary forest, and their borders. In elevation it mostly ranges up to 750 m (2,460 ft). Behavior Feeding The slate-throated gnatcatcher's diet is poorly known, but it is probably small arthropods like those of other Polioptila gnatcatchers. To feed it actively moves through the canopy and sub-canopy, and lower at the forest edges. It follows mixed-species foraging flocks singly or in pairs. Breeding No information has been published about the slate-throated gnatcatcher's breeding phenology. Vocalization The slate-throated gnatcatcher's most frequent vocalization is \"a short, rather faint, ascending trill, 'trrrrrrt'\" [1]. It also has a nasal mewing call [2]. References", "shortSummary": "The slate-throated gnatcatcher (Polioptila schistaceigula) is a species of bird in the family Polioptilidae. It is found in Colombia, Ecuad…", "locations": ["哥伦比亚", "厄瓜多尔", "巴拿马", "原始森林", "次生林"], "lat": 4.0, "lng": -72.0, "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/79/Polioptila_schistaceigula_-_Slate-throated_Gnatcatcher_-_male_%28cropped%29.jpg/960px-Polioptila_schistaceigula_-_Slate-throated_Gnatcatcher_-_male_%28cropped%29.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-polioptila", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-polioptila-schistaceigula", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-polioptila", "species": "taxonomy-species-polioptila-schistaceigula"}, "expandable": true, "x": -338.21, "y": -362.3, "z": -183.66}], "links": [{"key": "bird-slate-throated-gnatcatcher-cefccbe4__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species